f="https://lobste.rs/s/paulo7/simple_lists_tiny_do_list_app_written_old"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 03 Oct 2021 13:18:29 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Do you practice?</title><link>https://lobste.rs/s/h45sn7/do_you_practice</link><description>&lt;p&gt;In his talk &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4B00hV3wmMY&amp;amp;t=997s" rel="ugc"&gt;Solving the Right Problems for Engine Programmers&lt;/a&gt; Mike Acton’s first segment is about how new programmers are usually incompetent in three fundamental ways: practice, reasonable defaults, and problem solving.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;He goes on to say that most programmers do not practice, i.e., they do not take time out of their schedule to practice using the tools (languages, APIs, databases, whatever). I’ve been thinking about this for a while and it seems that a lot of professions have practice, but in the tech industry we don’t, we mostly go with sink or swim.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So my question is: do you have a regular practice? What is it like? Do you have tips and hints and recommendations for others?&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 03 Oct 2021 08:53:40 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>JShelter</title><link>https://jshelter.org/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/gelcga/jshelter"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 04 Oct 2021 05:04:21 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Shiner ESB, an Apple Network Server prototype, and what it did at Netscape/MCom</title><link>http://oldvcr.blogspot.com/2021/10/shiner-esb-apple-network-server.html</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/vnsdzv/shiner_esb_apple_network_server"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 04 Oct 2021 10:15:55 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Realtek wireless firmwares imported</title><link>https://undeadly.org/cgi?action=article;sid=20211004070841</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/ock4oo/realtek_wireless_firmwares_imported"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 04 Oct 2021 02:54:19 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>How Big Tech Runs Tech Projects and the Curious Absence of Scrum</title><link>https://blog.pragmaticengineer.com/project-management-at-big-tech/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/8ncqtt/how_big_tech_runs_tech_projects_curious"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 03 Oct 2021 21:55:56 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>The Story Behind an Open Source Software Un-Maintenance (2020)</title><link>https://ploum.net/the-story-behind-an-open-source-software-un-maintenance/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/lsyahs/story_behind_open_source_software_un"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 04 Oct 2021 06:59:59 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Dune: A shell by the beach</title><link>https://github.com/adam-mcdaniel/dune</link><desc